  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Pat your <strong>haddock bites</strong> dry with kitchen paper and cut into large bite-sized chunks</p><p>Add the <strong>haddock chunks</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>cornflour, </strong>a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, a grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and your <strong>five-spice mix</strong> and give everything a good mix up until well coated</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1657108033197-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1657108033197-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1657108033197-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1657108033197-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1657108033197-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once the pan is very hot, add the <strong>coated haddock</strong> and cook for 3-4 min on each side or until golden and crispy and the fish is cooked through – this is your <strong>crispy haddock</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1657108037139-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1657108037139-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1657108037139-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1657108037139-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1657108037139-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the haddock is cooking, finely slice your <strong>red chilli[es]</strong> into rounds</p><p>Trim, then roughly chop your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>into batons</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s] </strong>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and slice into thin strips</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1657108041379-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1657108041379-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1657108041379-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1657108041379-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1657108041379-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>fine egg noodles</strong> to a pot and cover them with <strong>boiled water</strong> until fully submerged</p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 1-2 min or until tender, then drain, reserving a cup of <strong>starchy noodle water</strong></p><p>Once drained, return the noodles to the pot and set aside</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1657108045334-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1657108045334-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1657108045334-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1657108045334-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1657108045334-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the haddock is crispy, add the <strong>spring onion batons </strong>to the pan with the <strong>chilli rounds </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Cook for 2-3 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, transfer everything to a plate (save the pan!) and set aside until serving – this is your <strong>salt & pepper haddock</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1657108049088-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1657108049088-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1657108049088-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1657108049088-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1657108049088-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>pepper strips </strong>and cook<strong> </strong>for 2 min or until slightly softened</p><p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>soy sauce </strong>and<strong> toasted sesame oil</strong> in a small bowl with your <strong>rice vinegar</strong> – this is your <strong>sesame dressing</strong></p><p>Wash<strong> </strong>your<strong> spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1657108053029-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1657108053029-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1657108053029-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1657108053029-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1657108053029-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the pepper is cooked, add the <strong>drained noodles </strong>and <strong>spinach</strong> to the pan</p><p>Tip: Add a splash of the starchy noodle water if it's looking a little dry</p><p>Turn off the heat and stir through the <strong>sesame dressing </strong>– these are your <strong>sesame noodles</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1657108057376-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1657108057376-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1657108057376-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1657108057376-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1657108057376-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve up your<strong> sesame noodles </strong>with your <strong>salt & pepper haddock </strong>to one side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
